The aim of these codes is to produce Lensing Power Spectrum from input 3D matter power spectrum.
The 3D power spectrum in generated by either using camb (http://camb.info) and the Cosmic Emulator (http://www.lanl.gov/projects/cosmology/CosmicEmu/emu.html). The python code make_params.py is used to generate the 3D Power spectrum.
table.txt is parameter file downloaded from the paper 
Any list of parameters allowed by the emulator will work.

The file params.x is the a parameter file for camb.
The parameter file params_redshifts.x is a parameter file for camb that includes all redshifts in the file zfile.txt
First run make_params.py. This code uses params.x and params_redshifts.x.
Then run cambpkforshear.py and emupkforshear.py.
These two codes cast the output in a form that is usable by the C++ codes. 


The Cl codes are written in C++. These codes use the publicly available gsl libraries (http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/).
Type make to create the execuatbles.
The configfile cambconfig_1.config is an example configfile.

The C++ codes require a configfile of the form:
//This code takes the power spectrum from the camb and returns the shear power spectrum.
// call [paramfile]
// 
// 
// om h^2 (This includes dark matter and baryonic matter)
// omb h^2
// ns
// sigma_8
// w
// h
// name of the file containing the matter power spectrum (Example: /users/astro/sdeb/camb/NLResults/concat.dat)
// name of the outputfile for Cl's
// name of the file containing redshifts
// alpha (Photoz parameters Ma Hu & Huterer)
// beta
// na
// sigmaz
// zbias
// kmax
// id  (id=0 represents camb, id=1 represents Emulator. This is important since emulator does not require multiplication by h.)
// zbin (This is an array of the form 0.6 1.2 2.0 3.0)
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

